      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAMMA SAYS SO (8) returned in good order off a short break, being 0.9L off the winner at Ascot last time out in a stronger race than this. Back to maiden company here looks a good move and Brad Parnham remains in the saddle. Can lob into a midfield position and land the knockout blow. MAYTHISBETHEONE (7) led them up but couldn't sustain the effort last time out over 1200m here, finishing 1.9L off the winner. Back to 1100m here may hold the key and she has enough speed to roll across from the wide alley. Ticks a few boxes here and can get the job done without surprising. BUDERIM (1) is first-up here on the back of a trial win at Lark Hill. He was solid over 1200m on debut here back in July and if he can return in similar fashion, he can make a statement. LONGTIMEBELIEVER (3) hasn't been far away in recent efforts and can be in the finish. CASSENITE (2) can sit much closer today as she finally draws a barrier and she can go close.",
